cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.IT, cs.SY 

The paper introduces a novel method for inferring directional relations from time series data using deep learning models to discover nonlinear relations. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with complex relational structures, which could fall under the social and information networks (cs.SI) sub-category. The method also involves regularization, which could fall under the information theory (cs.IT) sub-category. Finally, the paper applies the method to a video game environment and a heart-rate vs. breath-rate dataset, which suggests that it could also belong to the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category.
